								A world of investments for your clients
							














With managed funds from Macquarie, you can help your clients gain exposure to Australian and international shares, fixed income, infrastructure securities and alternatives.











Finding opportunities that matter for clients







Macquarie Investment Management
A global asset manager with offices throughout Australia, the United States, Europe and Asia, we prioritise autonomy and accountability at the team level in pursuit of opportunities that matter for clients. Our conviction-based, long-term approach to investing has led clients to entrust us to manage more than $300 billion1. In Australia we offer both Macquarie strategies and those managed by other world-class investment managers through the Macquarie Professional Series.











Macquarie Professional Series
Macquarie has searched the world for what we believe are the most outstanding investment managers and have partnered with a select few to bring their signature investment strategies to you and your clients.
They include Analytic Investors LLC, Arrowstreet Capital, Independent Franchise Partners, Polaris Capital Management LLC, Walter Scott & Partners and Winton Capital Management.




























About Australian shares
For more than a quarter of a century, Macquarie has been a leading manager of Australian shares. Our team of more than 25 analysts rigorously researches and evaluates ASX-listed companies. We only invest in those we believe offer your clients the best value and opportunities.



 Macquarie High Conviction Fund A concentrated portfolio of our best ideas in Australian equities  Provides your clients with exposure to a concentrated portfolio of Australian shares that our investment team believes will generate the highest returns. The team's style-neutral, bottom-up portfolio construction process creates increased opportunity for more consistent long-term returns by not depending on the growth and value cycles of the share market. 


 Macquarie Australian Small Companies Fund Seeking exposure to the big opportunities in small companies  Aims to invest in a diversified selection of some of the fastest-growing Australian companies. Give your clients the potential for consistent returns, capital growth and some income. Our investment team identifies potentially attractive 'value' and 'growth' stocks through proprietary quantitative screening and an intense fundamental research process. 

















About international shares
Most of the world's largest and most successful companies list on exchanges outside Australia. Also Asia's emerging markets provide exciting growth opportunities. We've searched the world for the most outstanding investment managers who can help your clients tap into the most exciting investment opportunities, wherever they may be.



 Analytic Global Managed Volatility Fund Global equities with low volatility  Aims to provide a low-volatility and long-term global investment option. . The fund offers the potential for consistent above-index returns over the long term and provides access to Analytic, a pioneer in quantitatively-driven, low-volatility equity investment management. 


 Arrowstreet Global Equity Fund Long-term global equities exposure  Take a long-term approach to investing in global equities. Arrowstreet's fund managers take an active quantitative investment approach that aims to add value through varying market conditions. The fund invests in companies from developed and emerging markets. Macquarie offers unhedged and hedged versions of the fund. 




 IFP Global Franchise Fund Access to leading international brands  IFP's fund managers take a low turn-over, buy-and-hold approach to investing for the fund, with a focus on value and capital preservation. This means they only invest in approximately 20 to 40 high quality companies at a time and focus on businesses with high free cash flow and dominant intangible assets such as a brand, patent, or licences. Macquarie offers unhedged and hedged versions of the fund. 


 Macquarie Asia New Stars No.1 Fund Uncovering new opportunities in Asia  Your clients can capitalise on the potential capital growth of small and mid-sized companies in the world's most dynamic economic region. The fund provides exposure to small to mid-sized businesses in Asia, (excluding Japan), and aims to provide both capital growth and some income. Macquarie's fund managers take a rigorous, bottom-up approach to selecting stock and identifying investments with low valuations and high growth potential. 




 Polaris Global Equity Fund Access a diversified portfolio of value-oriented global equities  Provides exposure to a diversified portfolio of global equities that Polaris believes are the most attractive value opportunities. The fund is actively managed, using a benchmark-unaware, bottom-up, research-driven approach with a focus on sustainable free cash flow. It generally holds between 65 and 100 securities of globally-listed companies, including those in emerging markets and small capitalisation companies. 


 Walter Scott Emerging Markets Fund Access growth companies in emerging markets  Help your clients access the high-growth potential of companies in emerging markets. Walter Scott's bottom-up, fundamental approach to investing focuses on companies from developing economies that offer long-term growth potential. Walter Scott's experienced fund managers pay particular attention to factors such as strong earnings growth, high return on equity and high free cash flow. 




 Walter Scott Global Equity Fund High-growth companies in global markets  Walter Scott scours global markets for what it believes are the world's best companies. Its fundamental, bottom-up investment approach combines detailed financial analysis with business and industry analysis. Your clients can benefit from Walter Scott's selective stock picking and ability to target companies capable of sustainable wealth generation. Macquarie offers unhedged and hedged versions of the fund. 

















About fixed income
Fixed income investments, such as government and corporate bonds, can provide regular income and capital growth for your clients and can help mitigate the risk of investing too heavily in one asset class. Macquarie has over 30 years of fixed income experience and can offer your clients some of what we believe are the best opportunities from around the world.



 Macquarie Diversified Fixed Interest Fund A defensive and multi-sector bond solution  Offers exposure to a diversified portfolio of fixed interest and credit-based investments. Macquarie's fund managers aim to provide a regular income and some capital growth by actively identifying outperforming fixed interest and credit sectors. The fund also minimises currency volatility through hedging. 


 Macquarie Income Opportunities Fund An income solution with a focus on preserving capital  Attempts to provide a regular income at a better rate of return than bank or term deposits by giving your clients exposure to interest-bearing securities issued by a range of different companies. The fund's capital preservation focus means it invests in a diversified portfolio of highly liquid securities. 

















About alternatives
Governments and companies increasingly use private investment to fund large infrastructure projects such as roads, airports and hospitals. Investing in this important asset class offers your clients the potential for stable, inflation-linked income, capital growth and portfolio diversification. Meanwhile, our absolute return fund also has the potential to generate positive returns, even in falling markets.



 Macquarie International Infrastructure Securities Fund Exposure to the global infrastructure assets  Offers your clients a global portfolio of listed infrastructure securities. The fund invests across both developed and emerging markets, as well as across infrastructure sectors. Investment decisions are only made after Macquarie's large specialist infrastructure team has conducted intensive fundamental research. Macquarie offers unhedged and hedged versions of the fund. 


 Winton Global Alpha Fund Diversification to traditional portfolios  Aims to generate long-term returns for your clients through a specialised managed futures trading strategy. With the potential to generate positive returns in both rising and falling markets, the fund can provide valuable portfolio diversification benefits. Winton's investment team's model-driven, automated approach to trading involves analysing market trends and then developing mathematically-based strategies to capitalise on them. 















 



