Macquarie Investment Management Limited Key Developments

Macquarie Investment Management Hires Thomas Hobson as Associate Director, Insurance Solutions
May 24 17
Macquarie Investment Management has hired Thomas Hobson, CFA as associate director, insurance solutions. Hobson is responsible for expanding the firm's asset management relationships with insurers. Hobson joins Macquarie from BlackRock Investment Management where he most recently served as relationship manager and head of business development for retail financial institutions. He reports to Brett Wright, co-head of client group, Macquarie Investment Management, Americas, and is based in Philadelphia. Prior to his tenure at BlackRock, Hobson was a director of product strategy for Nationwide Investment Management. He also held various roles at Morgan Stanley Investment Management and The Vanguard Group.


Australia and New Zealand Banking Group Partners with Macquarie for New Wrap Platform
Feb 3 16
Macquarie Investment Management has inked an agreement with Australia and New Zealand Banking Group (ANZ) to develop a new wrap platform for ANZ's advice partners. Under the agreement, Macquarie will offer administration services presently offered through Oasis, ANZ's wholly owned business. At present, Oasis manages $6.9 billion in funds and serves over 50,000 customers. Employees in Oasis are expected to be reduced over the next 18 months as services are transitioned to Macquarie. The transition is slated to be completed within 18 months, with the new platform expected to be rolled out from May 2016.


Macquarie Investment Management Appoints Dominic Janssens as Global Chief Operations Officer, Effective April 4
Feb 1 16
Macquarie Investment Management announced that Dominic Janssens will join the organization as its new global chief operations officer, based at its global headquarters in Philadelphia. In this role, Janssens’ responsibilities will include developing the strategy to optimize and scale MIM’s global platform in areas including investment operations, administration, controls, fund accounting, business management and financial and management analysis. Janssens joins from T. Rowe Price, where he has been the director of Global Investment and Institutional Client Services since 2008. Janssens will join the organization on April 4 and will report to Ben Bruck, the global head of Macquarie Investment Management and the chairman of Delaware Investments. While based in Philadelphia, he will oversee MIM’s operational groups in Sydney as well as those in Delaware Investments in Philadelphia.


